<<set $d4 = -1>>

(The classroom feels strangely quiet.  
Warm light, but the air is heavy.)
Hina stands at the back of the room, looking at the empty seat.
Hina:Today makes it exactly one week.  
Mio has been missing for seven days.
(Two students whisper near the door.)
StudentA:Did you hear? The police labeled it as a runaway.
StudentB:But her mom was on the news as a kidnapping suspect.  
How could that be the same as “running away”…?

StudentA:I don’t know. Teacher said we shouldn’t talk about it.  
Everyone’s avoiding her name now.
(Hina listens quietly, gripping her bag strap.)
Hina:Everyone cared so much at first.  
Hina:But after the news… everything changed.  
Hina:It feels like… if they don’t talk about her, she’ll disappear.
Hina:Her things are still here.  
Hina:She didn’t run away. I know she didn’t.
Hina:Her locker… Maybe there’s a clue inside.
===
title: MioDesk
---
(Mio’s desk isn’t messy, but it hasn’t been reorganized in a long time.  
Everything is in the places she always used… like time just stopped here.)

On the desk:
Half-finished math notes, a pen without its cap,  
slightly warped sticky notes with faint water marks,  
a couple of extracurricular books stacked loosely,  
a workbook with a folded corner,  
a convenience store receipt with simple items.
Hina:
She didn’t disappear on purpose.  
It just feels like… she was about to come back.
<<jump MioDeskOptions>>
===
title: MioDeskOptions
---
What should I look at?
    -> Read the notebook
        (A notebook lies on the desk, filled with fragmented sentences.)
        “I want to feel warm.”  
        “I want to feel loved.”  
        “I want to taste something that doesn’t disappear.”
        Hina:…What was she writing?  
        This isn’t like her usual notes.
        <<jump MioDeskOptions>>
    -> Notice the feather
        (Near the leg of the desk, almost hidden by the chair,  
        there’s a small white feather on the floor.)
        Hina:…A feather?  
        Why would something like this be here…?
        She stares at it for a moment, then looks away.
        <<jump MioDeskOptions>>
    -> Check the small details
        Hina:Stickers, smudged notes, a warped memo with water marks…  
        Like she drank a sip of water, wrote a few lines—  
        and something interrupted her halfway.
        Hina gently runs her fingers along the desk edge.
        Hina:…What happened to you that day?
        <<jump MioDeskOptions>>
    -> Leave
    Hina:I should look around the rest of the classroom too.

===
title: PigeonFeather
---
A white feather under Mio’s chair.
Hina: A pigeon? Indoors?  
She hesitates, then pockets it.
