Hina:…I wrote that.  
Hina:We were supposed to buy cake together.
===
title: TrashCan
---
(The trash can holds only crumpled worksheets and old tests.)
Hina:None of this is hers.  
Just normal school trash.
===
title: PottedPlant
---
(A slightly wilted plant, soil dry and cracked.)
Hina:She watered this every morning…
(Hina touches a leaf.)
Hina (thought):Now… no one takes care of it.
===
title: NoticeBoard
---
(The notice board is crowded with flyers.)
Club recruitment, festival posters,  
exam countdowns,  
an old missing notice,  
and a half-torn “Seeking Witnesses”.
Hina:Everyone moves on…  
Hina:Only these papers still remember she was here.
===
title: TeacherDesk
---
(A pile of half-graded homework on the teacher’s desk.)
Some pages say: “Good effort, but be more precise.”  
The duty roster still has Mio’s name on this week.  
A blue mug sits beside it—water still warm.
Hina:Teacher…  
Hina:Are you pretending nothing happened too?
===
title: Gossip
---
(Two more classmates whisper in a corner.)
StudentC:Do you think… Mio actually ran away with her mom?
StudentD:I don’t know. The paper said her mom owed a lot of money.  
Maybe… she really did something bad.
(Hina clenches her fist, jaw tight.)
Hina:…Impossible.
Hina:Mio would never.
